Name: AddressType

Name: AdministrativeGender
Title: AdministrativeGender
Descriptino: The gender of a person used for administrative purposes.

Name: AppointmentCancellationReason
Title: Appointment cancellation reason
Descriptino: This example value set defines a set of reasons for the cancellation of an appointment.

Name: PracticeSettingCodeValueSet
Title: Practice Setting Code Value Set
Descriptino: This is the code representing the clinical specialty of the clinician or provider who interacted with, treated, or provided a service to/for the patient. The value set used for clinical specialty has been limited by HITSP to the value set reproduced from HITSP C80 Table 2-149 Clinical Specialty Value Set Definition.

Name: ContactPointSystem
Title: ContactPointSystem
Descriptino: Telecommunications form for contact point.

Name: ContactPointUse
Title: ContactPointUse
Descriptino: Use of contact point.

Name: ContactEntityType
Title: Contact entity type
Descriptino: This example value set defines a set of codes that can be used to indicate the purpose for which you would contact a contact party.

Name: DaysOfWeek
Title: DaysOfWeek
Descriptino: The days of the week.

Name: ParticipantType
Title: Participant type
Descriptino: This value set defines a set of codes that can be used to indicate how an individual participates in an encounter.

Name: EncounterReasonCodes
Title: Encounter Reason Codes
Descriptino: This examples value set defines the set of codes that can be used to indicate reasons for an encounter.

Name: Identifier Type Codes
Title: IdentifierType
Descriptino: A coded type for an identifier that can be used to determine which identifier to use for a specific purpose.

Name: IdentifierUse
Title: IdentifierUse
Descriptino: Identifies the purpose for this identifier, if known .

Name: CommonLanguages
Title: Common Languages
Descriptino: This value set includes common codes from BCP-47 (http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47)

Name: LinkType
Title: LinkType
Descriptino: The type of link between this patient resource and another patient resource.

Name: LocationMode
Title: LocationMode
Descriptino: Indicates whether a resource instance represents a specific location or a class of locations.

Name: LocationType
Title: Location type
Descriptino: This example value set defines a set of codes that can be used to indicate the physical form of the Location.

Name: LocationStatus
Title: LocationStatus
Descriptino: Indicates whether the location is still in use.

Name: Marital Status Codes
Title: MaritalStatus
Descriptino: This value set defines the set of codes that can be used to indicate the marital status of a person.

Name: NameUse
Title: NameUse
Descriptino: The use of a human name.

Name: OrganizationType
Title: Organization type
Descriptino: This example value set defines a set of codes that can be used to indicate a type of organization.

Name: ParticipantRequired
Title: ParticipantRequired
Descriptino: Is the Participant required to attend the appointment.

Name: PatientContactRelationship
Title: Patient Contact Relationship
Descriptino: The nature of the relationship between the patient and the contact person.

Name: Program
Title: Program
Descriptino: This value set defines an example set of codes that could be can be used to classify groupings of service-types/specialties.

Name: ServiceCategory
Title: Service category
Descriptino: This value set defines an example set of codes that can be used to classify groupings of service-types/specialties.

Name: ServiceProvisionConditions
Title: ServiceProvisionConditions
Descriptino: The code(s) that detail the conditions under which the healthcare service is available/offered.

Name: ReferralMethod
Title: ReferralMethod
Descriptino: The methods of referral can be used when referring to a specific HealthCareService resource.

Name: ServiceType
Title: Service type
Descriptino: This value set defines an example set of codes of service-types.

Name: JurisdictionValueSet
Title: Jurisdiction ValueSet
Descriptino: This value set defines a base set of codes for country, country subdivision and region    for indicating where a resource is intended to be used.             Note: The codes for countries and country subdivisions are taken from    [ISO 3166](https://www.iso.org/iso-3166-country-codes.html)    while the codes for "supra-national" regions are from    [UN Standard country or area codes for statistical use (M49)](http://unstats.un.org/unsd/methods/m49/m49.htm).

Name: Hl7VSBedStatus
Title: hl7VS-bedStatus
Descriptino: Value Set of codes that specify the state of a bed in an inpatient setting, and is used to determine if a patient may be assigned to it or not.

Name: Hl7VSAppointmentReasonCodes
Title: hl7VS-appointmentReasonCodes
Descriptino: Value Set of codes that describe the kind of appointment or the reason why an appointment has been scheduled.

Name: ServiceDeliveryLocationRoleType
Title: ServiceDeliveryLocationRoleType
Descriptino: A role of a place that further classifies the setting (e.g., accident site, road side, work site, community location) in which services are delivered.

Name: GenderIdentityValueSet
Title: Gender Identity Value Set
Descriptino: This valueset specifies terms which represent an individual's personal experience of being a woman, man, nonbinary, or how the person prefers to self-describe. People may identify with more than one gender identity or use different gender identities in different settings. This resource is an informative value set; a normative subset containing the expanded values can be found on Canada Health Infoway's [Terminology Server](https://infocentral.infoway-inforoute.ca/en/tools/standards-tools/terminology-server).

Name: RecordedGenderValueSet
Title: Recorded Gender Value Set
Descriptino: The scope of this subset is to represent genders as used in healthcare data systems. This includes commonly used gender identities for administrative and clinical purposes. This resource is an informative value set; a normative subset containing the expanded values can be found on Canada Health Infoway's [Terminology Server](https://infocentral.infoway-inforoute.ca/en/tools/standards-tools/terminology-server).

Name: RecordedGenderTypeValueSet
Title: Recorded Gender Type Value Set
Descriptino: The scope of this subset is to represent types of sex and gender that are used in healthcare data systems. This includes commonly used gender identities for administrative and clinical purposes. This resource is an informative value set; a normative subset containing the expanded values can be found on Canada Health Infoway's [Terminology Server](https://infocentral.infoway-inforoute.ca/en/tools/standards-tools/terminology-server).
